

KOTSHOP

KOTSHOP is thoughtfully designed to deliver a smooth, dependable, and user-friendly experience for everyday food shopping.

The application emphasizes simplicity, clarity, and efficiency, allowing users to interact with it naturally and without confusion.

Every feature is carefully structured to ensure predictable behavior, fast response, and ease of use.

The app is lightweight and accessible, making it suitable for a wide range of users and environments.

By focusing on essential food categories and intuitive controls, KOTSHOP reduces unnecessary complexity while still providing accurate feedback and reliable results.

The overall goal is to make food selection quick, transparent, and comfortable for everyone.

GUIDELINES

All food items are displayed in the form of buttons for quick and direct interaction.

Left mouse click on an item button will increase (increment) the quantity of that item.

Right mouse click on the same item button will decrease (decrement) the quantity.

Item quantities cannot be reduced below zero to maintain accuracy and prevent errors.

A “Done” button is positioned at the bottom-right (south-east) of the application.

The “Done” button remains inactive until at least one item has been incremented.

Once an item is selected, the “Done” button becomes active and can be clicked.

After clicking “Done”:

A receipt is generated automatically.

The receipt displays all selected items, along with their prices and quantities.

A tax-inclusive total price is calculated and shown at the bottom of the receipt.

For responsible spending, the final tax-affected total price must be equal to or less than the amount entered by the user in the price input field.

These guidelines ensure that KOTSHOP remains simple, reliable, and easy to use from selection to checkout.